-- Peru Stocks: Cementos Lima, Credicorp, Minsur, Siderperu
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-11T21:18:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/peru-stocks-cementos-lima-intergroup-siderperu.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 3:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.1 percent to 23,270.01. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.1 percent to 2,958.74.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, rose 2.2 percent to 2.84 soles after U.S. stocks
rebounded, said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 1.1 percent to $134.50 after Chief Executive
Officer Walter Bayly said Peruvian lending is slated to expand
20 percent this year.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA known as Siderperu, advanced 1 percent to 99 centimos.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, rose 1 percent to $1 after copper gained in
 London .  Minsur SA (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell 2.3 percent to 2.96 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
